<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="820" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.711/801</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1916</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3680. Consul at Singapore telegraphs following:</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>Information shows Dutch steamer <hi rend="italic">Tjikembang, en
                                    route</hi> Manila to Java ports, was brought Singapore July 5 by
                                British naval authorities and Manila mails searched. Replies to
                                inquiries addressed local officials apparently indefinitely delayed.
                                Also mails from Manila, Spanish steamer <hi rend="italic">Eizaguirre</hi>, searched this port July 27.</p>
                        </quote>
                        <p>Please communicate to Foreign Office with appropriate protest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>